    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Learn about this from a</p>

<p><a href="python%20bug%20discussion">http://bugs.python.org/issue12459</a></p>

<p>When you call <code>sleep(-1)</code>) in Windows, it means sleep infinitely. Possible use case is to put an application in sleep unTIL waken up by signal.</p>

<p>Seems like only Windows do that.</p>
